With the latest update, I lost the ability to "Move Existing Tag." The checkbox is still there(http://screencast.com/t/RE0Ukn1rRf), but it gives me the message that the tag already exists.

{code}
! [rejected]        tag-name -> tag-name (already exists)
{code}

Here are the cli commands that I do that _work_:
{code}
- > git tag [tag-name] -f
- > git push --tags -f
{code}

This used to work from within Source Tree... (before 1.8) maybe in the 1.7 versions.

