{code}
/git-repo
{code}

I should be able to open this repository even if invoking the {{stree .}} from

{code}
/git-repo/src/main
{code}

This is at least how {{gitx}} works.

When I set "Select all files when selecting commit" to 0, it always behaves as 1 unless I manually select one or more files in the list of possible files to commit.

I confirm that "Select all files when selecting commit" is set to 0 by running the following:
{code}
defaults read com.torusknot.SourceTreeNotMAS selectAllFilesOnCommitSelection
{code}

I use homebrew-cask to install my applications on OS X 10.9. Generally cask installs applications to /opt/homebrew-cask/Caskroom/ and then sym links them in /Applications. For example:

{code}
$ ls -lA /Applications/Kaleidoscope.app
 
lrwxr-xr-x  1 craig  admin    67B  3 Nov 23:14 /Applications/Kaleidoscope.app@ -> /opt/homebrew-cask/Caskroom/kaleidoscope/2.0.1_114/Kaleidoscope.app
{code}

In SourceTree, I open "Preferences" > "Diff" and set the "Visual Diff Tool" to "Kaleidoscope", when I try to close the "Preferences" screen I get an error stating:

{quote}
Kaleidoscope Not Found

Kaleidoscope was not found on this Mac, please install it before selecting it as an external diff or merge tool.
{quote}

*EDIT*
I originally guessed the issue was because Kaleidoscope was symlinked, but I just installed Kaleidoscope directly in {{/Applications}} and the issue is still present.
